{"title_page": "NHL 08", "text_new": "{{For|the NHL season starting in 2008|2008\u201309 NHL season}}\n\n{{Infobox video game\n|title = NHL 08\n|image = NHL 08 Coverart.jpg\n|caption = [[Eric Staal]] on the cover of ''NHL 08''\n|developer = [[EA Canada]] (PS3, Xbox 360)<br>[[HB Studios]] (PS2, PC)\n|publisher = [[EA Sports]]\n|series = [[NHL (video game series)|''NHL'' series]]\n|engine =\n|released = {{Video game release|NA|September 11, 2007|NA|September 12, 2007 <small>(X360)</small>|AU|September 20, 2007 <small>(PC, X360)</small>|EU|September 21, 2007 <small>(PC, X360)</small>|AU|September 21, 2007 <small>(PS3)</small>|EU|September 27, 2007 <small>(PS3)</small>|AU|October 11, 2007 <small>(PS2)</small>|EU|October 12, 2007 <small>(PS2)</small>}}\n|genre = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n|modes = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]]\n|platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]]<br>[[PlayStation 2]]<br>[[PlayStation 3]]<br>[[Xbox 360]]\n}}\n'''''NHL 08''''' is a [[video game]] released on September 11, 2007 in [[North America]]; the [[Xbox 360]] version was supposed to be released on the same date as the [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 2]] and [[PlayStation 3]] versions,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/shippin-out-september-10-14-heavenly-sword-nhl-skate/1100-6178472/ |title=Shippin' Out September 10\u201314: Heavenly Sword, NHL, Skate |website=[[GameSpot]] |date=September 10, 2007 |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref> but was postponed for a day due to shipping issues.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\n==Gameplay==\n''NHL 08'' features a new and improved \"Skill Stick System,\" which EA says will allow gamers to more easily control the puck.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/nhl-08-first-look/1100-6172299/|title=NHL 08 First Look|last=Ekberg|first=Brian|date=June 11, 2007|website=GameSpot|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930080624/http://www.gamespot.com/ps3/sports/nhl08/news.html?sid=6172299&om_act=convert&om_clk=newlyadded&tag=newlyadded;img;1|archivedate=September 30, 2007|url-status=live|accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref> ''NHL 08'' also includes \"Goalie Mode,\" where users can control their team's goalie with a new third-person camera. Another new feature is the ability to create custom plays, where you can take part in creating custom plays in practice mode.\n\n===Gameplay modes===\n'Dynasty Mode' allows users to create a dream team and play through to the [[Stanley Cup]], however, there is no fantasy draft on the current generation version of the game ([[Xbox 360]], [[PlayStation 3]]), only on the PC and [[PlayStation 2]] versions.\n\nThe game features the-then 29 teams of the [[American Hockey League]] (AHL).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theahl.com/news/league/index.html?article_id=7813 |title=AHL featured in EA's NHL 08 |publisher=[[American Hockey League]] |date=June 12, 2007 |accessdate=June 17, 2008 |archivedate=June 5, 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080605230629/http://www.theahl.com/news/league/index.html?article_id=7813}}</ref> Players can develop talent through the AHL, and then call up their prospects to play in the NHL. Every AHL team is fully playable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.easports.com/nhl08/features.jsp |title=EA SPORTS NHL 08 Features Page |accessdate=June 17, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080702080258/http://www.easports.com/nhl08/features.jsp |archivedate=July 2, 2008 }}</ref> Sweden's [[Swedish Hockey League|Elitserien]] and Finland's [[Liiga|SM-liiga]] are also included on the Xbox 360 and PlayStation. However, the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]] (DEL) and [[Slovak Extraliga]] are only to be found on the PC and PlayStation 2 versions.\n\n==Reception==\nThe PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 versions received \"favorable\" reviews, while the PlayStation 2 and PC versions received \"mixed or average reviews\", according to the [[Review aggregator|review aggregation]] website [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPS3\"/><ref name=\"MCX360\"/><ref name=\"MCPS2\"/><ref name=\"MCPC\"/>\n\n''[[Games for Windows: The Official Magazine]]'' gave it a score of five out of ten.<ref name=\"Games for Windows\">{{cite journal |last=Goble |first=Gord |title=NHL 08: Skill-Stick, Same Old Shtick |magazine=[[Games for Windows: The Official Magazine]] |issue=11 |date=October 2007 |page=69 |publisher=Ziff Davis Media}}</ref> The game won [[GameSpot]]'s \"Best Sports Game of 2007\" award.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\n{{Video game reviews\n| PC = true\n| align      = left\n| PS2 = true\n| PS3 = true\n| X360 = true\n| na = true\n| EGM_PS3 = 9.17/10<ref name=EGM>{{cite journal |author=EGM staff |title=NHL 08 (PS3, X360) |magazine=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]] |date=October 2007 |page=87}}</ref>\n| EGM_X360 = 9.17/10<ref name=EGM/>\n| EuroG_X360 = 7/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Lahti |first=Evan |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/nhl-08-review |title=NHL 08 (X360) |website=[[Eurogamer]] |date=October 14, 2007 |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GI_PS3 = 8.5/10<ref name=GI>{{cite journal |last=Reiner |first=Andrew |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/NR/exeres/EF78F795-F592-4179-A016-EE93D3519441.htm |title=NHL 08 (PS3, X360) |magazine=[[Game Informer]] |issue=174 |date=October 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080125123727/http://www.gameinformer.com/NR/exeres/EF78F795-F592-4179-A016-EE93D3519441.htm |archivedate=January 25, 2008 |url-status=dead |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| GI_X360 = 8.5/10<ref name=GI/>\n| GamePro_X360 = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Dagley |first=Andrew |url=http://gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox360/games/reviews/140668.shtml |title=Review: NHL 08 vs. NHL 2K8 (X360) |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=October 16, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071017000027/http://gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox360/games/reviews/140668.shtml |archivedate=October 17, 2007 |url-status=dead |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GameRev_PS3 = C<ref name=GameRev>{{cite web |last=Damiano |first=Greg |url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/nhl-08 |title=NHL 08 Review (PS3, X360) |publisher=[[Game Revolution]] |date=October 22, 2007 |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GameRev_X360 = C<ref name=GameRev/>\n| GSpot_PC = 6/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Navarro |first=Alex |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/nhl-08-review/1900-6179019/ |title=NHL 08 Review (PC) |website=GameSpot |date=September 18, 2007 |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| GSpot_PS2 = 6.5/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Navarro |first=Alex |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/nhl-08-review/1900-6179018/ |title=NHL 08 Review (PS2) |website=GameSpot |date=September 18, 2007 |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| GSpot_PS3 = 8.5/10<ref name=GSpot>{{cite web |last=Navarro |first=Alex |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/nhl-08-review/1900-6178762/ |title=NHL 08 Review (PS3, X360) |website=GameSpot |date=September 13, 2007 |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| GSpot_X360 = 8.5/10<ref name=GSpot/>\n| GSpy_PS3 = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=GSpy>{{cite web |last=Vasconcellos |first=Eduardo |url=http://ps3.gamespy.com/playstation-3/nhl-08/820956p1.html |title=GameSpy: NHL 08 (PS3, X360) |publisher=[[GameSpy]] |date=September 18, 2007 |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GSpy_X360 = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=GSpy/>\n| GameZone_PS2 = 7/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Bedigian |first=Louis |url=http://www.gamezone.com/reviews/nhl_08_ps2_review |title=NHL 08 - PS2 - Review |publisher=GameZone |date=September 11, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081004030316/http://ps2.gamezone.com/gzreviews/r32134.htm |archivedate=October 4, 2008 |url-status=live |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GameZone_PS3 = 8.9/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Lafferty |first=Michael |url=http://www.gamezone.com/reviews/nhl_08_ps3_review |title=NHL 08 - PS3 - Review |publisher=GameZone |date=September 10, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081006085436/http://ps3.gamezone.com/gzreviews/r32134.htm |archivedate=October 6, 2008 |url-status=live |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GameZone_X360 = 9/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Hopper |first=Steven |url=http://www.gamezone.com/reviews/nhl_08_360_review |title=NHL 08 - 360 - Review |publisher=GameZone |date=September 16, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081006074948/http://xbox360.gamezone.com/gzreviews/r32134.htm |archivedate=October 6, 2008 |url-status=live |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| IGN_PS3 = 8.6/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldstein |first=Hilary |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2007/09/10/nhl-08-review |title=NHL 08 Review (PS3) |website=[[IGN]] |date=September 10, 2007 |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| IGN_X360 = 8.9/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldstein |first=Hilary |url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/819/819016p1.html |title=NHL 08 Review (X360) |website=IGN |date=September 10, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070913122857/http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/819/819016p1.html |archivedate=September 13, 2007 |url-status=dead |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| OXM_X360 = 8.5/10<ref>{{cite journal |title=NHL 08 |magazine=[[Official Xbox Magazine]] |date=October 2007 |page=73}}</ref>\n| PCGUS_PC = 35%<ref>{{cite journal |title=NHL 08 |magazine=[[PC Gamer]] |date=December 25, 2007 |page=83}}</ref>\n| PSM_PS3 = 8.5/10<ref>{{cite journal |title=Review: NHL 08 (PS3) |magazine=[[PlayStation: The Official Magazine|PSM]] |date=December 2007 |page=82}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev1_X360 = A<ref>{{cite news |last=Zuniga |first=Todd |url=http://www.avclub.com/article/nhl-08-7539 |title=NHL 08 (X360) |newspaper=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=September 24, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011045835/http://avclub.com/content/games/nhl_08 |archivedate=October 11, 2007 |url-status=live |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_PC = 65/100<ref name=\"MCPC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/nhl-08 |title=NHL 08 for PC Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_PS2 = 70/100<ref name=\"MCPS2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-2/nhl-08 |title=NHL 08 for PlayStation 2 Reviews |website=Metacritic |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_PS3 = 86/100<ref name=\"MCPS3\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/nhl-08 |title=NHL 08 for PlayStation 3 Reviews |website=Metacritic |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_X360 = 85/100<ref name=\"MCX360\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/nhl-08 |title=NHL 08 for Xbox 360 Reviews |website=Metacritic |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== Legacy ==\nNHL 08 was included in ''[[EA Sports 08 Collection]]'' in 2008 along with ''[[Madden NFL 08]]'', ''[[Tiger Woods PGA Tour 08]]'', ''[[FIFA 08]]'' and ''[[NBA Live 08]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |date= |url=https://www.gamespot.com/ea-sports-08-collection |title=EA Sports 08 Collection |website=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=January 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{moby game|id=/nhl-08}}\n\n{{NHL series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nhl 08}}\n[[Category:2007 video games]]\n[[Category:Electronic Arts games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 2 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 3 games]]\n[[Category:Xbox 360 games]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:NHL (video game series)]]\n[[Category:EA Sports games]]\n[[Category:Video games set in 2007]]\n[[Category:Video games set in 2008]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Canada]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the NHL season starting in 2008|2008\u201309 NHL season}}\n\n{{Infobox video game\n|title = NHL 08\n|image = NHL 08 Coverart.jpg\n|caption = [[Eric Staal]] on the cover of ''NHL 08''\n|developer = [[EA Canada]] (PS3, Xbox 360)<br>[[HB Studios]] (PS2, PC)\n|publisher = [[EA Sports]]\n|series = [[NHL (video game series)|''NHL'' series]]\n|engine =\n|released = {{Video game release|NA|September 11, 2007|NA|September 12, 2007 <small>(X360)</small>|AU|September 20, 2007 <small>(PC, X360)</small>|EU|September 21, 2007 <small>(PC, X360)</small>|AU|September 21, 2007 <small>(PS3)</small>|EU|September 27, 2007 <small>(PS3)</small>|AU|October 11, 2007 <small>(PS2)</small>|EU|October 12, 2007 <small>(PS2)</small>}}\n|genre = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n|modes = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]]\n|platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]]<br>[[PlayStation 2]]<br>[[PlayStation 3]]<br>[[Xbox 360]]\n}}\n'''''NHL 08''''' is a [[video game]] released on September 11, 2007 in [[North America]]; the [[Xbox 360]] version was supposed to be released on the same date as the [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 2]] and [[PlayStation 3]] versions,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/shippin-out-september-10-14-heavenly-sword-nhl-skate/1100-6178472/ |title=Shippin' Out September 10\u201314: Heavenly Sword, NHL, Skate |website=[[GameSpot]] |date=September 10, 2007 |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref> but was postponed for a day due to shipping issues.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\n==Gameplay==\n''NHL 08'' features a new and improved \"Skill Stick System,\" which EA says will allow gamers to more easily control the puck.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/nhl-08-first-look/1100-6172299/|title=NHL 08 First Look|last=Ekberg|first=Brian|date=June 11, 2007|website=GameSpot|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930080624/http://www.gamespot.com/ps3/sports/nhl08/news.html?sid=6172299&om_act=convert&om_clk=newlyadded&tag=newlyadded;img;1|archivedate=September 30, 2007|url-status=live|accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref> ''NHL 08'' also includes \"Goalie Mode,\" where users can control their team's goalie with a new third-person camera. Another new feature is the ability to create custom plays, where you can take part in creating custom plays in practice mode.\n\n===Gameplay modes===\n'Dynasty Mode' allows users to create a dream team and play through to the [[Stanley Cup]], however, there is no fantasy draft on the current generation version of the game ([[Xbox 360]], [[PlayStation 3]]), only on the PC and [[PlayStation 2]] versions.\n\nThe game features the-then 29 teams of the [[American Hockey League]] (AHL).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theahl.com/news/league/index.html?article_id=7813 |title=AHL featured in EA's NHL 08 |publisher=[[American Hockey League]] |date=June 12, 2007 |accessdate=June 17, 2008 |archivedate=June 5, 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080605230629/http://www.theahl.com/news/league/index.html?article_id=7813}}</ref> Players can develop talent through the AHL, and then call up their prospects to play in the NHL. Every AHL team is fully playable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.easports.com/nhl08/features.jsp |title=EA SPORTS NHL 08 Features Page |accessdate=June 17, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080702080258/http://www.easports.com/nhl08/features.jsp |archivedate=July 2, 2008 }}</ref> Sweden's [[Swedish Hockey League|Elitserien]] and Finland's [[Liiga|SM-liiga]] are also included on the Xbox 360 and PlayStation. However, the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]] (DEL) and [[Slovak Extraliga]] are only to be found on the PC and PlayStation 2 versions.\n\n==Reception==\nThe PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 versions received \"favorable\" reviews, while the PlayStation 2 and PC versions received \"mixed or average reviews\", according to the [[Review aggregator|review aggregation]] website [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPS3\"/><ref name=\"MCX360\"/><ref name=\"MCPS2\"/><ref name=\"MCPC\"/>\n\n''[[Games for Windows: The Official Magazine]]'' gave it a score of five out of ten.<ref name=\"Games for Windows\">{{cite journal |last=Goble |first=Gord |title=NHL 08: Skill-Stick, Same Old Shtick |magazine=[[Games for Windows: The Official Magazine]] |issue=11 |date=October 2007 |page=69 |publisher=Ziff Davis Media}}</ref> The game won [[GameSpot]]'s \"Best Sports Game of 2007\" award.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\n{{Video game reviews\n| PC = true\n| align      = left\n| PS2 = true\n| PS3 = true\n| X360 = true\n| na = true\n| EGM_PS3 = 9.17/10<ref name=EGM>{{cite journal |author=EGM staff |title=NHL 08 (PS3, X360) |magazine=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]] |date=October 2007 |page=87}}</ref>\n| EGM_X360 = 9.17/10<ref name=EGM/>\n| EuroG_X360 = 7/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Lahti |first=Evan |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/nhl-08-review |title=NHL 08 (X360) |website=[[Eurogamer]] |date=October 14, 2007 |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GI_PS3 = 8.5/10<ref name=GI>{{cite journal |last=Reiner |first=Andrew |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/NR/exeres/EF78F795-F592-4179-A016-EE93D3519441.htm |title=NHL 08 (PS3, X360) |magazine=[[Game Informer]] |issue=174 |date=October 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080125123727/http://www.gameinformer.com/NR/exeres/EF78F795-F592-4179-A016-EE93D3519441.htm |archivedate=January 25, 2008 |url-status=dead |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>\n| GI_X360 = 8.5/10<ref name=GI/>\n| GamePro_X360 = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Dagley |first=Andrew |url=http://gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox360/games/reviews/140668.shtml |title=Review: NHL 08 vs. NHL 2K8 (X360) |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=October 16, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071017000027/http://gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox360/games/reviews/140668.shtml |archivedate=October 17, 2007 |url-status=dead |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GameRev_PS3 = C<ref name=GameRev>{{cite web |last=Damiano |first=Greg |url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/nhl-08 |title=NHL 08 Review (PS3, X360) |publisher=[[Game Revolution]] |date=October 22, 2007 |accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| GameRev_X360 = C<ref name=GameRev/>\n| GSpot_PC = 6/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Navarro |first=Alex |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/nhl-08-review/1900-6179019/ |title=NHL 08 Review (PC) |website=GameSpot |date=September 18, 2007 |accessdate=June 28, 2015}}</ref>