anteri]]|FRA}}||Touriste-routier || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 11h 55' 24\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 56\n| {{flagathlete|[[\u00c9mile Faillu]]|FRA}}||Touriste-routier (Ile de France) || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 12h 57' 35\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 57\n| {{flagathlete|[[Georges Petit (cyclist)|Georges Petit]]|FRA}}||Touriste-routier || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 14h 14' 14\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 58\n| {{flagathlete|[[Pierre Bobo]]|FRA}}||Touriste-routier (Midi) || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 14h 37' 15\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 59\n| {{flagathlete|[[Marcel Ilpide]]|FRA}}||Touriste-routier (Midi) || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 15h 10' 18\"\n|}\n\n===Team classification===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Final team classification <ref name=\"veloarchive\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://hemeroteca.elmundodeportivo.es/preview/1930/07/28/pagina-1/1397122/pdf.html |agency=El Mundo Deportive |language=Spanish |date=28 July 1930 |title=En la general por Andres L\u00e9ducq por equipos, Francia triunfa \u00a1\u00a1por fin!! en su gran prueba ciclista |accessdate=30 September 2009 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5kEXe5Pol?url=http://hemeroteca.elmundodeportivo.es/preview/1930/07/28/pagina-1/1397122/pdf.html |archive-date=2 October 2009 |url-status=live |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Rank!! scope=\"col\" | Team!! scope=\"col\" | Time\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |1\n| France || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 517h 34' 09\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |2\n| Belgium || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 1h 48' 55\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |3\n| Germany || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 5h 09' 59\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |4\n| Italy || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 6h 32' 42\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |5\n| Spain || style=\"text-align:right;\" | + 6h 42' 50\"\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Final regional team classification <ref>{{cite news|url=http://ouestfrance.cd-script.fr/opdf/1930/07/29/85/1930-07-29_85_07.pdf|work=l'Ouest-Eclair|language=French|date=29 July 1930|ti