{"title_page": "\u00d8ivind Bolstad", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = \u00d8ivind Bolstad\n| image = \n| caption =  \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date|df=y|1905|2|1}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{Death date and age|df=y|1979|5|7|1905|2|1}}\n| death_place = \n| monuments = \n| residence = \n| nationality = Norwegian\n| other_names = \n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| occupation = Playwright, novelist\n| years_active = \n| employer = \n| organization = \n| agent = \n| known_for = \n| notable_works = \n| style = \n| influences = \n| influenced = \n| home_town = \n| television = \n| religion = \n| spouse = \n| partner = \n| children = \n| parents = \n| relatives = \n| awards = [[Dobloug Prize]]\n}}\n'''\u00d8ivind Bolstad''' (1 February 1905 \u2013 7 May 1979) was a [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]] playwright and novelist.\n\nBolstad was born at [[Vard\u00f8]] in [[Finnmark]], Norway. \nHe made his literary breakthrough with the novel ''Den r\u00f8de begonia'' from 1947.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=\u00d8ivind Bolstad |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/\u00d8ivind_Bolstad |language=Norwegian | accessdate=22 October 2010 }}</ref> \nBolstad published a number of short stories and narratives in both Norwegian and foreign magazines as well as a series of books and narrations.\n\nIn 1973 he became the recipient of the [[Dobloug Prize]] literature award in 1973.<ref name=dobloug>{{cite web | url=http://www.forfatterportalen.no/litteraturpriser/dobloug.htm | title=Dobloug-prisen  |publisher=Forfatterportalen.no |language=Norwegian |accessdate=22 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Selected works==\n* ''De gylne lenker'' &ndash; (1945)\n* ''Den r\u00f8de begonia'' &ndash; (1947)\n* ''Profit\u00f8ren'' &ndash; (1947)\n* ''Gamle Winckels testament'' &ndash; (1949)\n* ''Sp\u00f8kefuglen p\u00e5 Toska. Historier fra strilelandet'' &ndash; (1955)\n* ''Fortellinger og fabler'' &ndash; (1966)\n* ''D\u00f8dens tango'' &ndash; (1967)\n* ''Apassionata'' &ndash; r (1968)\n* ''Jorunn'' &ndash; (1969)\n* ''Bergensikon'' &ndash; (1970)\n* ''Sort messe'' &ndash; (1970)\n* ''Bolstad forteller'' &ndash; (1971)\n* ''Tilgi oss ikke for Helene'' &ndash; (1975)\n* ''Duell med d\u00f8den'' &ndash; (1977)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Dobloug Prize winners}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bolstad, Oivind}}\n[[Category:1905 births]]\n[[Category:1979 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Finnmark]]\n[[Category:20th-century Norwegian novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Norwegian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Norwegian male novelists]]\n\n{{Norway-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = \u00d8ivind Bolstad\n| image = \n| caption =  \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date|df=y|1905|2|1}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{Death date and age|df=y|1979|5|7|1905|2|1}}\n| death_place = \n| monuments = \n| residence = \n| nationality = Norwegian\n| other_names = \n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| occupation = Playwright, novelist\n| years_active = \n| employer = \n| organization = \n| agent = \n| known_for = \n| notable_works = \n| style = \n| influences = \n| influenced = \n| home_town = \n| television = \n| religion = \n| spouse = \n| partner = \n| children = \n| parents = \n| relatives = \n| awards = [[Dobloug Prize]]\n}}\n'''\u00d8ivind Bolstad''' (1 February 1905 \u2013 7 May 1979) was a [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]] playwright and novelist.\n\nBolstad was born at [[Vard\u00f8]] in [[Finnmark]], Norway. \nHe made his literary breakthrough with the novel ''Den r\u00f8de begonia'' from 1947.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=\u00d8ivind Bolstad |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/\u00d8ivind_Bolstad |language=Norwegian | accessdate=22 October 2010 }}</ref> \nBolstad published a number of short stories and narratives in both Norwegian and foreign magazines as well as a series of books and narrations.\n\nIn 1973 he became the recipient of the [[Dobloug Prize]] literature award in 1973.<ref name=dobloug>{{cite web | url=http://www.forfatterportalen.no/litteraturpriser/dobloug.htm | title=Dobloug-prisen  |publisher=Forfatterportalen.no |language=Norwegian |accessdate=22 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Selected works==\n* ''De gylne lenker'' &ndash; (1945)\n* ''Den r\u00f8de begonia'' &ndash; (1947)\n* ''Profit\u00f8ren'' &ndash; (1947)\n* ''Gamle Winckels testament'' &ndash; (1949)\n* ''Sp\u00f8kefuglen p\u00e5 Toska. Historier fra strilelandet'' &ndash; (1955)\n* ''Fortellinger og fabler'' &ndash; (1966)\n* ''D\u00f8dens tango'' &ndash; (1967)\n* ''Apassionata'' &ndash; r (1968)\n* ''Jorunn'' &ndash; (1969)\n* ''Bergensikon'' &ndash; (1970)\n* ''Sort messe'' &ndash; (1970)\n* ''Bolstad forteller'' &ndash; (1971)\n* ''Tilgi oss ikke for Helene'' &ndash; (1975)\n* ''Duell med d\u00f8den'' &ndash; (1977)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Dobloug Prize winners}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bolstad, Oivind}}\n[[Category:1905 births]]\n[[Category:1979 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Finnmark]]\n[[Category:20th-century Norwegian novelists]]\n[[Category:Norwegian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:20th-century Norwegian dramatists and playwrights]]\n\n\n{{Norway-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:duplicate categorization; already in subcat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%98ivind_Bolstad"}
